OL,3,CWomen 'need to work extra 19 years
OL,4,Ctypically to close pensions gender gap'
OL,6,FWomen face needing to work for an
OL,7,Fextra 19 years to retire with the same
OL,8,Fpension savings as men typically,
OL,9,Faccording to a report.
OL,11,FWomen retire on average with pension
OL,12,Fsavings of #69,000, compared with
OL,13,F#205,000 for men, the research by
OL,14,Fpensions provider NOW: Pensions and
OL,15,Fthe Pensions Policy Institute (PPI)
OL,16,Ffound.
OL,18,FCareer gaps, caring responsibilities,
OL,19,Fchildcare costs and lower earnings
OL,20,Fcontribute to women often having less
OL,21,Fmoney saved for retirement than men.
