OL,3,CWomen 'need to work extra 19 years
OL,4,Ctypically to close pensions gender gap'
OL,6,FAs automatic enrolment into workplace
OL,7,Fpensions starts at the age of 22, the
OL,8,F19-year gender pension gap means a
OL,9,Fgirl would need to start saving for
OL,10,Fretirement from three years old in
OL,11,Forder to have kept up with men by
OL,12,Fretirement age, researchers suggest.
OL,14,FBut women often live longer than men,
OL,15,Fmeaning their retirement pots also
OL,16,Fneed to last for longer.
OL,18,FNOW: Pensions said the #10,000
OL,19,Fearnings trigger for people to be
OL,20,Fautomatically enrolled into a
OL,21,Fworkplace pension should be removed.
