OL,3,CWomen 'need to work extra 19 years
OL,4,Ctypically to close pensions gender gap'
OL,6,FJoanne Segars, chairwoman of trustees
OL,7,Fat NOW: Pensions, said: "It's hard to
OL,8,Fbelieve that by the time a young girl
OL,9,Fstarts school at four, she will
OL,10,Falready be falling behind a boy of the
OL,11,Fsame age when it comes to providing
OL,12,Ffor her retirement. Yet this is the
OL,13,Freality many girls face as they leave
OL,14,Feducation and enter the world of work.
