OL,3,CWomen 'need to work extra 19 years
OL,4,Ctypically to close pensions gender gap'
OL,6,F"While there are some pensions policy
OL,7,Foptions that could be introduced to
OL,8,Fpotentially mitigate the gender
OL,9,Fpension gap, it's unlikely to
OL,10,Fsignificantly reduce without changes
OL,11,Fin labour market conditions and
OL,12,Fgendered divisions of domestic labour."
OL,14,FThe research used various sources of
OL,15,Fdata, including Office for National
OL,16,FStatistics (ONS) and Department for
OL,17,FWork and Pensions (DWP) figures.
