OL,3,CWomen 'need to work extra 19 years
OL,4,Ctypically to close pensions gender gap'
OL,6,F"Alongside this, our expansion of free
OL,7,Fchildcare in England means working
OL,8,Ffamilies could save an average of
OL,9,F#6,500 per child per year, and we
OL,10,Frecently published the first official
OL,11,Fmeasure of the gender pensions gap,
OL,12,Fwhich will help track the collective
OL,13,Fefforts of government, industry and
OL,14,Femployers to close it."
OL,16,FBefore the introduction of automatic
OL,17,Fenrolment in 2012, just 55% of
OL,18,Feligible employees saved into a
OL,19,Fworkplace pension, but by 2021 this
OL,20,Fhad risen to 88%, the Government has
OL,21,Fpreviously said.
